From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Fri, 3 Jul 2026 10:24:50 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] make: tolerate unmakeable OPTIONAL includes; overlay: mkdir
 uses the merged view
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Fixes the '-include blah fails with No rule and nothing works' regression
the optional-include-remake change introduced, with GNU's ACTUAL
semantics (measured, not assumed): a -include file whose remake can't
happen — no producer at all, a producer whose recipe fails, or a
producer whose own prerequisite is unbuildable — is silently tolerated
and the build proceeds. Implemented as a separate quiet exec pass for
optional remake targets (required ones stay strict), with the failed
names carried across the re-parse (SARUN_KATI_NOREMAKE env on the
shadow re-exec, a local set on the builtin retry loop) so a permanently
unmakeable include can't loop to the depth cap. exec_opts' quiet mode
also suppresses the '*** [target] Error' banner and no-rule notes,
matching GNU's silence. Three corpus cases pin the shapes; both
corpora 398/408 fail=0.

overlay: mkdir's existence check used layer() (this box's upper + raw
host) while lookup serves resolve() (the merged parent-chain view) — a
path hidden by a parent-box whiteout / opaque dir / OCI
no_host_fallback returned EEXIST from mkdir yet ENOENT from stat, so
create_dir_all never reconciled (sibling-session report). mkdir now
guards on resolve().

Co-Authored-By: Claude Fable 5 <noreply@anthropic.com>
Claude-Session: https://claude.ai/code/session_01B97aMMA3rHQW7gsyBB2Cpa
